/*------------------------------------------------------------------
 MBlue Nav-Style Sidebar Vista (Ver. 0.4.5)

Author: M.BLUE - Tested on: Firefox 3.5.1 - Last Update: 20.07.2009
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Description:
 1. Gives the Nav-Buttons style to the Sidebar.
 2. Skins the Sidebar header, buttons, splitter, grippy,
    toolbars, background, etc.
 3. Skins the BOOKMARK/HISTORY Panel.
 4. Supports "All-in-One Sidebar" extension.
 5. Supports "Clear Fields" extension.
 6. Hides AIOS useless menuitems.
 7. Highly Customizable.
 8. Integrates with the other "Nav-Style" styles.
 9. Integrates with the other "Nav-Style Sidebar Vista" styles for
    supporting Downloads-Panel, Addons-Panel, and more Extension
    Panels (TabSidebar, TagSifter, etc.).
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Notes:
-This style skins AIOS and the Bookmarks/History Panels ONLY, but
 it can integrate with other "Nav-Style Sidebar" styles for
 more extensions support (read below).

-Works with or without AIOS. Better results with AIOS installed.
 
-Supports both small and large icons (works better with small).
 
-Do not use other styles that changes the Sidebar settings.

-All-in-One Sidebar:
 This Style is optimized to use only a few of the features of AIOS.
 To make it work well, open the AIOS Options and disable all the
 extra Toolbars features. You should also disable Multipanel,
 Error Console and Extra Panels (they are useless and looks bad
 inside the sidebar). Only the Bookmarks & History Panels are
 supported (read below how to use more panels).
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Downloads-panel:
 If you have AIOS installed and want to use the Downloads-Panel in
 the Sidebar, you need the "Nav-Style Sidebar Vista (Downloads)"
 style.

Addons-panel:
 If you have AIOS installed and want to use the Addons-Panel in
 the Sidebar, you need the "Nav-Style Sidebar Vista (Addons)"
 style.

More Extensions-panels:
 If you want more sidebar Extensions skinned, you also need the
 "Nav-Style Sidebar Vista (EXT. NAME)" style that supports the
 Extension panel you want to skin.
--------------------------------------------------------------------
CUSTOMIZING:

 1. SIDEBAR HEADER BACKGROUND COLOR.
 2. SIDEBAR TITLE COLOR/SIZE/WEIGHT/OPACITY/ALIGN.
 3. BOOKMARKS/HISTORY TOOLBAR BG COLOR.
 4. NAV-STYLE ITEMS OPACITY.
 5. ICONS OPACITY.
 6. BOOKMARKS & HISTORY TEXTBOXES COLOR/SIZE/WEIGHT/OPACITY/ALIGN.
 7. BOOKMARKS & HISTORY PANELS OPACITY/STRIPED COLORS.
 8. BOOKMARKS PANEL TEXT COLOR/SIZE/WEIGHT.
 9. BOOKMARKS PANEL BACKGROUND COLOR.
10. HISTORY PANEL TEXT COLOR/SIZE/WEIGHT.
11. HISTORY PANEL BACKGROUND COLOR.
12. GRIPPY BACKGROUND COLOR/OPACITY.

> GO TO BOTTOM OF THE PAGE TO CUSTOMIZE
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Supported Extensions:
 All-in-One Sidebar (AIOS), Clear Fields.

Integrates with:
 MBlue Combine Nav-Buttons Vista
 MBlue Nav-Style Url-Bar Vista
 MBlue Nav-Style Buttons Vista
 MBlue Nav-Style Tabs Vista
 MBlue Nav-Style Statusbar Vista
 MBlue Nav-Style Throbber Vista
 MBlue Nav-Style Bookmarks-Bar Vista
 MBlue Nav-Style Awesome-Bar Vista
 MBlue Nav-Style Menubar Vista
 MBlue Nav-Style Popup Vista
>MBlue Nav-Style Sidebar Vista
 MBlue Nav-Style Sidebar Vista (Downloads, Addons, Extensions)
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Updates:
20.07.2009 Ver. 0.4.5 = added support for FF 3.5
16.04.2009 Ver. 0.4.1 = supports new AIOS, again
22.12.2008 Ver. 0.4.0 = supports both old and new AIOS,
                        added namespace
03.10.2008 Ver. 0.3.1 = better integration, added striped options
16.09.2008 Ver. 0.3.0 = ready to release
...
10.09.2008 Ver. 0.2.0 = temp version done
...
31.08.2008 Ver. 0.1.0 = temp version
------------------------------------------------------------------*/



